[1] Canine, raccoon - Florida
Date: Wed 1 Sep 2010
Source: NBC-2.com [edited]
<http://www.nbc-2.com/Global/story.asp?S=13084230>


Charlotte County issued a rabies warning Wednesday [1 Sep 2010] after
a pit bull attacked and killed a rabid raccoon. The attack happened
north of Bermont Road and just west of Swaying Palm Drive. The
Charlotte county man and his dog Chance had an unfortunate run-in
with a raccoon on their Punta Gorda farm.

"I went and got a piece of PVC pipe because I was going to whack it.
Chance came out of nowhere and he just jumped on that thing, flipped
it in the air, and shook it and broke its back," said the Charlotte
County resident. Animal Control says the raccoon tested positive for
rabies. It issued a rabies alert to all residents living in east Punta Gorda.

Juergensen says there are several signs [in animals] residents should
be on the lookout for. "You have something called the dumb rabies
where the animal appears to be intoxicated. It staggers, falls over,
things like that. Then you have aggressive rabies where the animal is
full on aggressive. Juergensen says if you suspect an animal is
rabid, avoid it and call animal control immediately.

"It is a deadly disease if you were to contract it and not know it
and not go through the treatment," said Juergensen.

Luckily Chance had his rabies vaccination, but he's not out of the
woods yet. He has to remain in quarantine for the next 6 months.

