[2] Bat, human exposure - Idaho
Date: Fri 3 Sep 2010
Source: NBCMontana.com, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
<http://www.nbcmontana.com/news/24871091/detail.html>


Public health officials say 3 more people in the Wood River Valley
are undergoing rabies vaccines after encounters with aggressive bats
during the past week.

The Idaho Mountain Express reports one person that was bitten and 2
more that may have been bitten were being vaccinated as a precaution.
The encounters happened in Bellevue, Hailey, and Ketchum.

The rabies virus infects the central nervous system and is almost
always fatal once symptoms appear.

