[Imperial is located in Chase County, south west Nebraska, which can
be seen on the map at
<http://www.digital-topo-maps.com/county-map/nebraska.shtml>. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

[The theme of many of the rabies updates is vaccination could have
prevented tragedy. Some states or areas within states that hare
having an increase in wild animal rabies should perhaps consider the
oral rabies vaccine baits. Of course, such a course is dependent upon
many factors including which animal is the primary problem.

This last story illustrates that any animal can be susceptible to
rabies. This moderator has long advocated that if you are working
with that animal in a capacity that brings you into frequent contact,
then rabies vaccination should be part of your protocol, and at the
very least a discussion with your veterinarian.

There is one other interesting fact pointed out in the last article
and that is the amount of PEP (post exposure prophylaxis) available
in any given area. Perhaps that is a discussion for county medical
planners or other responsible medical officials within an area. - Mod.TG]
